<DOC><DOCNO> AP890915-0105 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-15-89 1244EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--TaxiHijack     09-15 0144</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Taxi Hijack,0146</SECOND><HEAD>Taxi Hijacker Surrenders Hostages</HEAD><DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A gunman demanding morphine hijacked ataxi Friday and took two hostages on an eight-hour ride throughCopenhagen before he was arrested, police and news reports said. Noone was injured.   The 34-year-old hijacker, wielding a sawed-off shotgun,commandeered the cab, took the driver hostage and later forced a27-year-old woman into the taxi, news reports said.   The man contacted police on radio, demanding morphine and asyringe, and said he planned to kill himself with an overdose.Newspaper reports said he was distraught over family problems.   Police followed the taxi at a discreet distance as it drovethrough the city streets for eight hours.   The ordeal ended when police promised to let the man go free andhe released the hostages. He was later arrested in a Copenhagenapartment, they said.</TEXT></DOC>